He was still looking down at the ground this entire time. He was busy contemplating a lot of things. Not even Yoshimura understood why things had ended this way until he finally got it. What his father meant when he said that something was wrong with him. It was exactly the same thing that ended up being his own demise that would kill him and his mother. “I... I’m sorry, please forgive me. I didn’t know what I was doing until after what I had done. I wasn’t in the right state.” He frowned. “Since the beginning of this game, I could feel myself slipping away from my own body, but I was too scared to say anything in fear of someone taking advantage of it.” Yoshimura looked up from his podium and took his hands out from his hoodie to reveal his bruised knuckles in shame. “I’ve now just realized that the only thing that I should’ve feared...” “was myself.” Yoshimura was about to cry right there and then, but something different happened. His face contorted into a twisted smile as tears fell down his face. Then, he let out such an awful laugh, and it stayed like that for several minutes until he closed his eyes and gripped the podium. “You know...” “I wonder if this is how my mother felt once she realized my father knew there was no saving her. I think I understand what that horrible sound of shattering glass and cracking was now.” Yoshimura smiled. However, this wasn’t the same smile he had on when he was himself. This was the smile of a broken man.
